        Island” because it is privately owned and cannot be visited without an
        invitation from one of the <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">225</NUMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">inhabitants</ENAMEX>. Most of the <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">residents</ENAMEX> are
        <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">pure-blooded Hawaiians</ENAMEX> who speak the language. The <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">men</ENAMEX> are engaged in
        ranching operations for <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bruce Robinson</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">owner</ENAMEX> of the <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC">island</ENAMEX>; the women
