        (<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1939 to 1990</TIMEX>). Now turned back to the <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC">state</ENAMEX>, the <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC">island</ENAMEX> is littered
        with unexploded bombs. Cleanup is slow and expensive, but plans call
        for <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Kahoolawe</ENAMEX> to become a cultural reserve. Until then, it remains
